{"word":"G2368 - θυμίαμα - thymíama - thoo-mee'-am-ah - Incense","slug":"G2368","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">θυμίαμα</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>thymíama"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>thoo-mee'-am-ah"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Incense"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B8;&#x03C5;&#x03BC;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03B1;&#x03BC;&#x03B1; - thumiama</b> - <i>thoo-mee'-am-ah</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G2370\">G2370</a>; an <i>aroma</i>, that is, fragrant <i>powder</i> burnt in religious service; by implication the <i>burning</i> itself: - incense, odour."}]}